difference between sleep and join
---------------------------------

sleep()
-----

* sleep is a static method 

* sleep will prevent the thread for a particular time to dont excute anything

* may give interdmediate data if we sleep a thread in a big calculations.

* only one overlaoded method available

* it is a native method contains some code in native language


join()
------

* join is a non-static method 

* it will stop excuting until its another thread excutes.

* it will give the correct output after completion of the thread.

* There are so many overloaded methods available

* not a native method


